.org/wiki/OCLC\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:OCLC\">OCLC</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://worldcat.org/oclc/1008064829\">1008064829</a></small>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=VOENAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA4\">page 4</a>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation\" lang=\"en\">On one side lay the Ocean, and on one<br />Lay a great <b>water</b>, and the moon was full.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>\n<li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><b>1865</b>,  William Allingham (ed.),  <cite>The Ballad Book: a selection of the choicest British ballads</cite>, William and May Margaret, or the Water of Clyde:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation\" lang=\"en\">But ere he came to Clyde's <b>water,</b> fu' loud the wind did blaw.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>\n<li>A combination of water and other substance(s).\n<ol><li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\">sometimes&#32;<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#countable\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">countable</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac\">)</span> Mineral water.\n<dl><dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">Perrier is the most popular <b>water</b> in this restaurant.</i></div></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#countable\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">countable</a><span class=\"ib-comma\">,</span>&#32;often&#32;in the <a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#plural\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">plural</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/spa\" title=\"spa\">Spa</a> water.\n<dl><dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">Many people visit Bath to take the <b>waters</b>.</i></div></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\"><a href=\"