ple\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">Before your child is born, your <b>water(s)</b> will break. <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">North America</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span></i></div></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">Before the child is born, the pregnant womanâ€™s <b>waters</b> break. <span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\">UK</span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span></i></div></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#colloquial\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">colloquial</a><span class=\"ib-comma\">,</span>&#32;<a href=\"/wiki/medicine\" title=\"medicine\">medicine</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac\">)</span> Fluids in the body, especially when causing <a href=\"/wiki/swelling\" title=\"swelling\">swelling</a>.\n<dl><dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">He suffers from <b>water</b> on the knee.</i></div></dd></dl></li></ol></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#figurative\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">figuratively</a><span class=\"ib-comma\">,</span>&#32;in the <a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#plural\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">plural</a>&#32;or&#32;in the <a href=\"/wiki/singular\" title=\"singular\">singular</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac\">)</span> A state of affairs; conditions; usually with an adjective indicating an adverse condition.\n<dl><dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"en\">The rough <b>waters</b> of change will bring about the calm after the storm.</i></div></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#colloquial\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">colloqu